user_input: Does the RAK7289 support LoRa frame filtering?
retrieved_contexts: ['RAK7289 WisGate Edge Pro > RAK7289 WisGate Edge Pro > Product Features > Software > RAK7289 Features Overview', 'RAK7289 WisGate Edge Pro Datasheet > RAK7289 WisGate Edge Pro Datasheet > Overview > Product Features > Software > RAK7289 Features Overview [TABLE]', 'RAK7289 LoRaWAN Network Server Guide > RAK7289 LoRaWAN Network Server Guide > AWS IoT Core for LoRaWAN > Set up Your AWS Account and Permissions > Add the Gateway to AWS IoT > Frequency Band Selection and Role Setup > Supported LoRa Frequency Bands for RAK7289 [TABLE]', 'RAK7289 LoRaWAN Network Server Guide > RAK7289 LoRaWAN Network Server Guide > AWS IoT Core for LoRaWAN > Set up Your AWS Account and Permissions > Add the Gateway to AWS IoT > Frequency Band Selection and Role Setup > Supported LoRa Frequency Bands for RAK7289 [TABLE]', 'RAK7289 WisGate Edge Pro Datasheet > RAK7289 WisGate Edge Pro Datasheet > Specifications > Software > Software Features > RAK7289 Features Overview [TABLE]']
response: Yes, the RAK7289 WisGate Edge Pro supports **LoRa frame filtering**, which includes **node whitelisting**. This feature allows you to filter and control which LoRa nodes are permitted to communicate with the gateway.
reference: Yes, the RAK7289 WisGate Edge Pro supports LoRa Frame Filtering (node whitelisting) in Packet Forwarder mode.

user_input: What is the default IP address for RAK7268V2?
retrieved_contexts: ['RAK7268V2/RAK7268CV2 WisGate Edge Lite 2 Guide > RAK7268V2/RAK7268CV2 WisGate Edge Lite 2 Quick Start Guide > Product Configuration > Access the Gateway > WAN Port (Ethernet) > Access Gateway via WAN Port (Ethernet) [CODE]', 'RAK7268V2/RAK7268CV2 WisGate Edge Lite 2 Guide > RAK7268V2/RAK7268CV2 WisGate Edge Lite 2 Quick Start Guide > Product Configuration > Access the Gateway > WAN Port (Ethernet) > Access Gateway via WAN Port (Ethernet) [CODE]', 'RAK7268V2/RAK7268CV2 WisGate Edge Lite 2 Guide > RAK7268V2/RAK7268CV2 WisGate Edge Lite 2 Quick Start Guide > Product Configuration > Access the Gateway > WAN Port (Ethernet) > Access Gateway via WAN Port (Ethernet) [CODE]', 'RAK7268V2/RAK7268CV2 WisGate Edge Lite 2 Guide > RAK7268V2/RAK7268CV2 WisGate Edge Lite 2 Quick Start Guide > Product Configuration > Access the Gateway > WiFi AP Mode > Accessing RAK7268V2 Gateway via WiFi AP Mode', 'RAK7268V2/RAK7268CV2 WisGate Edge Lite 2 Guide > RAK7268V2/RAK7268CV2 WisGate Edge Lite 2 Quick Start Guide > Product Configuration > Access the Internet > Connect Through Ethernet > Access the Internet through Ethernet on RAK7268v2']
response:
The default IP address for the RAK7268V2 gateway depends on the connection method:

1. **Via WAN Port (Ethernet):**
   - The default IP is `169.254.X.X`, derived from the last 4 bits of the MAC address. For example, if the last 4 bits are `0F:01`, the gateway IP is `169.254.15.1`.

2. **Via WiFi AP Mode:**
   - The default IP address is `192.168.230.1`.
